---
title: `$anemon::set()`
description: Set or replace array value recursively.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Anemon::set(array &$input, $key, $value = null, $NS = '.');
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$array = [
    'foo' => 1,
    'bar' => [
        'baz' => 2,
        'qux' => 3
    ]
];

Anemon::set($array, 'bar.baz', '#');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$array = [
    'foo' => 1,
    'bar' => [
        'baz' => '#',
        'qux' => 3
    ]
];
~~~